}", "subject": "ocfs2: call o2quo_exit() if malloc failed in o2net_init()", "message": "ocfs2: call o2quo_exit() if malloc failed in o2net_init()

In o2net_init, if malloc failed, it directly returns -ENOMEM.  Then
o2quo_exit won't be called in init_o2nm.

